<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="336" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,610]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,438,222,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Diagnosis (Female):</emphasis>
Body length 2.7 mm (
<figureCitation box="[698,790,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); antenna with 37 antennomeres, longer than body; head behind eyes not narrowed (
<figureCitation box="[452,539,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); width of clypeus 2.0× its maximum height, with long hair (
<figureCitation box="[1213,1301,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); mandibles gradually widened basally (
<figureCitation box="[465,555,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); oral cavity not developed (
<figureCitation box="[882,972,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); length of eye in dorsal view as long as temple (
<figureCitation box="[246,340,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
); mesonotum with medio-posterior mesoscutal depression (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1119,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); notauli smooth (
<figureCitation box="[1332,1423,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); precoxal sulcus crenulate or rugose (
<figureCitation box="[566,651,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); pterostigma narrow, elongate, 3RSa vein as long as 2RS vein, m-cu vein interstitial, vein r originating almost middle of pterostigma, marginal cell almost reaching apex of wing (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
); first metasomal tergite 1.3× as long as its width at apex, gradually narrowing toward base; metasomal tergites black, metasomal sternites light brown; legs brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[858,948,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,961,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-217@4.[163,1424,957,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Biosteres (Chilotrichia) advectus Papp, 1979:A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, dorsal view; C. Head, frontal view; D. Head, lateral view; E. Mesosoma, dorsal view; F. Mesosoma, lateral view; G. Fore wing; H. Hind leg, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427830/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
); ovipositor sheaths short and not extended beyond apex of metasoma.
</paragraph>
